    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>Milewski covers the Haskell Monoid typeclass (mempty, mappend) and the distinction between point-free and pointwise equality. The examples below translate the same ideas into Scheme and Python. The free monoid on an alphabet is the set of all strings over that alphabet with concatenation; Haskell's String type with (++) is exactly this. Viewing monoids as single-object categories lets them compose with every other categorical construction.</p>

